算.definition: to regard as; to figure; to calculate; to compute

算不了.definition: does not count for anything; of no account

算了.definition: let it be; let it pass; forget about it

算你狠.definition: you got me!; you win!; you are something!

算力.definition: computing power; hash rate (digital currency mining)

算哪根蔥.definition: who do (you) think (you) are?; who does (he, she etc) think (he, she) is?

算數.definition: to count numbers; to keep to one's word; to hold (i.e. to remain valid); to count (i.e. to be important)

算準.definition: to calculate precisely; to identify; to discern; to tell

算老幾.definition: just who do (you) think (you) are? (or "just who does (she) think (she) is?" etc)

算計.definition: to reckon; to calculate; to plan; to expect; to scheme

算話.definition: (of sb's words) to count; can be trusted

算賬.definition: (accounting) to balance the books; to do the accounts; (fig.) to settle an account; to get one's revenge

算起來.definition: to calculate; to estimate; in total; all told; (fig.) if you think about it
